[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating JAXB Dependencies**\n\nI’m diving into the Gradle transitive dependency issue and how it relates to the activation API. The generated scaffold typically only adds target dependencies, but for JAXB to function properly, I need the right implementation on the classpath. I wonder if this means I’ll have to manage extra dependencies or if existing tests can avoid adding runtime dependencies. It sounds like I should check the Jakarta XML Bind documentation for clarification!\n\n**Analyzing JAXB Setup Requirements**\n\nI'm considering how the generated scaffold can test annotations and DatatypeConverter without requiring runtime. However, effective marshalling usually needs a runtime setup, which might mean an extra Maven dependency. I need to figure out whether I need concrete evidence to justify this additional setup. The Jakarta JAXB API POM only lists the activation-api and not an implementation provider, so I should check if org.glassfish.jaxb:jaxb-runtime matches the API version, especially for Jakarta XML Bind 4.1.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_049051927387c9d2016a3e9d3b524481949d1f267f49b9b81b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPp1F4Y2Ufu0bu2I35vnlRBjKoupDULw48rDtsooZ-Cniyc0OCupMK2SF29WKTGrZg42JbG11HCtrYe_bbuhan08a2zQ-3ziG1IX_9MvoqgY08GEjXyylFo-W30iXnE3Z8F5tX3kfwDbFW5Ptk0xnLuqzRsSNHFRfMOdqlp2upt9drF_yz6cuEjve5PwF-etjw44HODmh-blfALqFKaIsBEJv8fzwq1_6RbYWZIMqxx9_nkRZDDhpSxoYb7ZldcMpSu7xMmzYs_7znwCT0tdGv9fAu7eKDC9-90KyEfdY3jLRciyk4qoLaWOcZir-L3rsKIzzxeIzY0v0mmhLhJ2YbTlrwsNc9Sw8yLvx1Pl2VNmTi6yp6FCkws_AQGCBtaEmpFml1cU7lKH69dVTpGJNG_dyWLrwy6Aut80zdsF_rb88zkR9A3wkY1AztiEYUNM0pJyjR8jXZH-pwzl2jBxLwlCrb5dRTADGA5v8nCQi-sAN21Tth-Lb3GnWblpvZmDmFHl4RXuoax1M3am3TxeT8TzATqIsk6uYk2p1bYnwoltBZC7C4IztlIjfG_UVUas-85DEtFykDsprPPoCde0oix0Nsk8_cjf7erahKrg23HiCinSJEPnLa8Cv5VW5Cy3L52HUH4Xrv9uM9HcQqmYjbU2kqEVgsz0NGI1UL4TVOhQzX